description: Indicates if the file is REFRESHED/UPDATED/NOT APPLICABLE – literally “REFRESHED”, “UPDATED         ”  or“                                                     “
Literally “A”; indicates the end of the header record

RECORD INDICATOR TRANSFER TYPE; values include:
“A” = Incoming ACAT transfer
“B” = incoming Non-ACAT transfer
“C” = Incoming CIT transfer
“D” = Outgoing ACAT transfer
“E” = Outgoing Non-ACAT transfer
“F” = Outgoing CIT transfer
RECORD ID SEQUENCE NUMBER, begins with“00000001”
ACCOUNT NUMBER, including Office (3), Base Account (5), Check Digit (1)
INVESTMENT PROFESSIONAL (IP) NUMBER; NOTE: For three-character IP Numbers position 24 will be “”.

RECORD TYPE; value includes:
“3” = Mutual Fund Asset record

ASSET TYPE ID; values include:
“C” = CUSIP
“M” = Memo
ASSET NUMBER; if Asset Type ID in position 026 is “M” then this field will be zeroes and asset description becomes description of memo
ASSET STATUS; see Appendix T for values

ACTUAL QUANTITY SIGN; values include:
“+” = Positive Quantity
“-” = Negative Quantity
“” = Not Applicable

MARKET VALUE SIGN; values include:
“+” = Debit Amount
“-” = Credit Amount
“” = Not Applicable

CASH MARGIN INDICATOR; values include:
“C” = Cash
“M” = Margin
“S” = Short
NSCC METHOD OF DELIVERY CODE; see Appendix T for values

NETWORK INDICATOR; values include:
“Y” = Yes
“N” = No

DIVIDEND / CAPITAL GAIN CODE; values include:
“0” = Cash
“1” = Reinvest
“2” = Div-Cash/LTG-Cash/STG-Reinvest
“3” = Div-Cash/LTG-Reinvest/STG-Reinvest
“4” = Div-Cash/LTG-Reinvest/STG-Cash
“5” = Div-Reinvest/LTG-Cash/STG-Cash
“6” = Div- Reinvest/LTG-Reinvest/STG-Cash
“7” = Div- Reinvest/LTG-Cash/STG-Reinvest

BROKER DEALER INDICATOR; values include:
“Y” = Yes
“N” = No
“U” = Unknown

MUTUAL FUND DETAIL STATUS CODE; values include:
“A” = Pending Pershing Approval
“B” = Booked
“C” = Completed
“D” = Deleted - No Pending
“E” = Pending Dealer Change Form
“F” = Fund Processing Letter
“I” = Pending Instruction Letter to the Fund
“J” = Reject
“K” = Cancelled
“L” = Deleted - Pending Revision
“M” = Pending IBD Papers
“N” = Fund Processing - B52
“P” = Pending Pershing Instruction
“Q” = Completed - Tolerance Problem
“R” = Rejected - Both
“S” = Pending B50 / 3rd party instruction
“T” = Pending Transmission
“W” = Sent B50 / 3rd party instruction
“Z” = Rejected Pershing
ACTUAL FUND DATE, in CCYYMMDD format

REQUESTED QUANTITY INDICATOR; values include:
“F” = Full Position Requested
“P” = Partial Position Requested
REQUESTED QUANTITY; this will be zero when a Full Position is requested

REQUESTED QUANTITY SIGN; values include:
“+” = Positive Quantity
“-” = Negative Quantity
“” = Not Applicable
Literally “X”; indicates the end of detail record 3
Indicates if the file is REFRESHED/UPDATED/NOT APPLICABLE – literally “REFRESHED”, “UPDATED”, or “ ”
Literally “Z”; indicates the end of the trailer record
